title: Egypt: Egyptian-European Relations On Right Track - Ambassador
text:
Egypt: U.S. State Department - Egypt Able to Defeat Terrorism 
The Egyptian-European relations move on the right track in terms of the mutual visits of senior officials between the two sides, said Head of the European Union Delegation to Egypt Ambassador James Moran. 
Addressing the Egyptian Council for Foreign Affairs, Moran reviewed the bilateral ties between the Egyptian and European sides in addition to the amendments of the neighborhood policy between the two sides. 
"The new neighborhood policy will focus on a limited number of priorities that reflect common interests," he said, noting that issues like immigration, energy safety, combating terrorism, climate change, human rights, and judicial reform should be given a high priority. 
The European ambassador praised the economic reforms in Egypt during the last year as well as the new Suez Canal project. Egypt
